author: tkt
title: SMR (Sensory Motor Rythm)
subtitle_1: Used to achieve relaxed attention

author: tkt
title: Beta 1 - Sharpen the mind | 20 min | 19Hz
subtitle_1: A great way to get going in the morning without caffeine. This session helps reduce ADD and SAD symptoms. May cause anxiety.

author: tkt
title: Beta 2 - Sharpen the mind | 20 min | 23H
subtitle_1: Like Beta 1, but with a gigher target frequency range. May give a more energizing jor intense feeling.

author: tkt
title: Mental flexibility | 22 min | Variable
subtitle_1: To 'loosen up' a stuck mind. Can also be used for fibromyalgia.

author: tkt
title: 'Wise guy' Alpha | 30 min | 10.6Hz
subtitle_1: It has been shown that people with fast running alpha waves have higher than average IQs.

author: tkt
title: Coffee break Alpha | 15 min | 10Hz
subtitle_1: UGreat for a little rest during your coffee or lunch break.

author: tkt
title: Alpha Relaxer | 30 min | 12Hz
subtitle_1: Healthy alpha is 10 Hz. Most disorders have alpha slowing. This session reestablishes the natural alpha rhythm. Good for beginners.

author: tkt
title: Schumann Resonance | 22 min | 7.8Hz
subtitle_1: For a quick, through afternoon meditation. Calms 'hyper/chattery' minds. For those on the go.

author: tkt
title: Theta | 36 min | 5.5Hz
subtitle_1: Use for creative visualization. May also be used for sleep.

author: tkt
title: SMR for Reading | 20 min | 13Hz
subtitle_1: Improve attention and alertness while reading.

author: tkt
title: SMR/Beta | 24 min | 13.5Hz
subtitle: A gentle and entraining session that helps to focus mental functioning and memory.

author: tkt
title: Brain Booster | 30 min | 14Hz
subtitle: Use to impove mental functioning and memory, Based on Budzynski's study. Similar to ADD and learning, but with gentler transitions. Useful for seniors and those with ADD.

author: tkt
title: ADD and Learning | 26 min | 19Hz
subtitle_1: This session has rapid transitions for mental stimulation to help keep the user 'engaged' in the session. Used in the ADD study published in the journal of Neurotherapy.

author: tkt
title: Skill & Sports Development | 24 min | 18Hz
subtitle: Use this session to develop any skill or improve performance. Visualize feeling your best during the first half(alpha). Then visualize your perfect performance during the second half(beta) of the session.

author: tkt
title: Schumann for Sleep | 40 min | 7.8Hz
subtitle_1: For effective deep meditation and to improve the onset of sleep. Calms 'hyper/chattery' minds. Ideal for those with insomnia who have a busy mind and tense body.

author: tkt
title: Meditate to Sleep | 45 min | 4Hz
subtitle_1: A gentle and entraining session that helps to focus mental functioning and memory.

author: tkt
title: Alpha/Theta for Sleep | 36 min | 10Hz
subtitle_1: This session can really help to break up distressing thoughts that are interfering with sleep.

author: tkt
title: SMR for Sleep | 40 min | 14Hz
subtitle_1: This session has rapid transitions for mental stimulation to help keep the user 'engaged' in the session. Used in the ADD study published in the journal of Neurotherapy.

author: tkt
title: Delta | 45 min | 3.5Hz
subtitle1: To aid with falling asleep. Best for those with fibromyalgia.

author: tkt
title: Mood Booster 1 | 30 min | 8Hz
subtitle_1: Settles down negative emotions from the right brain while stimulating the left brain to rebalance alpha asymmetry.

author: tkt
title: Mood Booster 2 | 42 min | 8Hz
subtitle_1: This session has an alpha front end to reduce anxiety and enhance relaxation.

author: tkt
title: Sub-Delta | 24 min | 1Hz
subtitle: Mildly dissociating. Calms the hypothalamus. Beneficial for some with fibromyalgia and hypertension.

author: tkt
title: Extended Deep Alpha Relaxer | 80 min | 8.4Hz
subtitle_1: Stay relaxed for your dental, massage, physiotherapy, chiropractic and other appointments.

author: tkt
title: Paradise | 36 min | 6.5Hz
subtitle: A gentle slide down to Theta. Extroverts with low anxiety produce high levels of this frequency.
